## Content Organization

### Bilingual Support
The blog supports both Chinese and English:

- **Default (English)**: Content at root path `/`
- **Chinese**: Content under `/zh/` path
- Language switcher in navigation with localStorage preference

### Blog Posts
Posts are organized by date: `/YYYY/MM/DD/post-name/index.html`

Front-matter example (Chinese):
```yaml
---
title: InnoDB中B-tree(B+ tree)的加锁策略
date: 2025-11-12 22:35:51
tags: innodb, B tree, B+ tree
lang: zh-CN
---
```

Front-matter example (English):
```yaml
---
title: Understanding Snapshot Isolation Level
tags:
  - database
  - transaction
  - MVCC
categories:
  - database
comments: true
date: 2026-02-09 23:30:00
lang: en
---
```

### URL Patterns
| Page Type | URL Pattern |
|-----------|-------------|
| Home (EN) | `/` |
| Home (ZH) | `/zh/` |
| Post | `/YYYY/MM/DD/post-name/` |
| About | `/about/` |
| About (ZH) | `/zh/about/` |
| Archives | `/archives/` |
| Archives (ZH) | `/zh/archives/` |
| Category | `/categories/category-name/` |
| Tag | `/tags/tag-name/` |
| RSS Feed | `/atom.xml` |

## Development Workflow

### Content Publishing Process
1. Switch to `source` branch for development
2. Create/edit Markdown posts in `source/_posts/`
3. Run `hexo server` for local preview
4. Run `hexo generate` to build static files
5. Run `hexo deploy` to push to `main` branch
6. GitHub Pages automatically serves the updated content

### Common Hexo Commands
```bash
# Create a new post
hexo new post "Post Title"

# Create a new draft
hexo new draft "Draft Title"

# Publish a draft
hexo publish draft "Draft Title"

# Generate static files
hexo generate
# or
hexo g

# Clean generated files
hexo clean

# Start local server
hexo server
# or
hexo s

# Deploy to GitHub Pages
hexo deploy
# or
hexo d

# Generate and deploy
hexo g -d
```

### Git Workflow
```bash
# Switch to source branch for editing
git checkout source

# Make changes, then commit
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add new post about XXX"
git push origin source

# Generate and deploy
hexo clean
hexo generate
hexo deploy
```

## Build and Test Commands

### Local Development (source branch)
```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server (http://localhost:4000)
npm run server

# Build static files
npm run build

# Clean and rebuild
npm run clean && npm run build

# Deploy to GitHub Pages
npm run deploy
```

### Testing Checklist
Before deploying, verify:
- [ ] Posts render correctly
- [ ] Images display properly
- [ ] Code blocks have syntax highlighting
- [ ] Links work correctly
- [ ] Mobile responsive design
- [ ] Language switcher functions
- [ ] Comments load (Giscus)
- [ ] RSS feed is valid

## Code Style Guidelines

### Git Commit Messages
- Use **English** for all commit messages
- Follow conventional commits format:
  - `feat:` - New feature
  - `fix:` - Bug fix
  - `docs:` - Documentation
  - `style:` - Formatting
  - `refactor:` - Code refactoring
  - `chore:` - Maintenance

### Markdown Content
- Use YAML front-matter for metadata
- Tags can be comma-separated string or YAML list
- Include `lang: zh-CN` or `lang: en` for language
- Use relative paths for internal links

### HTML (Generated)
- Indentation: 2 spaces
- Semantic HTML5 elements
- Schema.org microdata for SEO
- h-card microformat for author info

### CSS
- Main stylesheet: `css/style.css`
- Based on Basscss utility classes
- Dark theme by default (`colorscheme: dark`)
- RTL support via `rtl.css`

### JavaScript
- jQuery-based (v3.x)
- Main file: `js/main.js`
- Search functionality: `js/search.js`
- Language preference stored in localStorage

## Testing Instructions

### Manual Testing Steps
1. Run `hexo server` and visit http://localhost:4000
2. Test navigation menu on mobile (hamburger icon)
3. Test language switcher (EN/ZH toggle)
4. Verify code copy buttons work
5. Check table of contents on long posts
6. Test search functionality
7. Verify Giscus comments load on posts with `comments: true`

### Validation
- RSS feed: Validate at https://validator.w3.org/feed/
- HTML: Check for valid markup
- Links: Check for broken links
- Images: Ensure all images have alt text

## Security Considerations

1. **No sensitive data** in repository (no API keys, passwords)
2. User-generated content handled by Giscus (GitHub Discussions)
3. Third-party resources:
   - Giscus loaded from `giscus.app`
   - All other libraries self-hosted in `/lib/`
4. Content Security Policy considerations for external scripts

## Deployment

- **Platform**: GitHub Pages
- **Branch**: `main` (default)
- **Build**: Automatic (for static files already in repo)
- **Custom Domain**: Not configured
- **HTTPS**: Enabled by default
- **Dependabot**: Enabled for npm dependencies

## Key Features

1. **Responsive Design** - Mobile-first, works on all devices
2. **Bilingual Support** - Chinese and English with language switcher
3. **Dark Theme** - Default dark color scheme
4. **Comments** - Giscus (GitHub Discussions integration)
5. **Local Search** - Client-side search functionality
6. **RSS Feed** - Atom format at `/atom.xml`
7. **Code Copy** - One-click copy for code blocks
8. **Table of Contents** - Auto-generated TOC for posts
9. **Social Links** - GitHub and email in header

## Maintenance Notes

### Adding New Posts
1. Work in `source` branch
2. Create post in `source/_posts/`
3. Use appropriate language tag (`lang: zh-CN` or `lang: en`)
4. Add tags and categories
5. Test locally before deploying

### Theme Updates
1. Cactus theme located in `themes/cactus/`
2. Custom config in `_config.yml` under `theme_config:`
3. Backup modifications before updating theme

### Dependency Updates
- Dependabot monitors npm dependencies
- Review PRs before merging
- Test build after updates

